annotation.TEXT: Also, that bonus room's border was blue, so no hidden 1-up there.
Well, I guess the Thwimps sort of imitate the pile-driver micro goombas in a way...
Gotcha!
Come on, gimme 50...

Now, I could activate the P-switch and run across down there, but I remember that hitting this ON/OFF block also made blocks appear down there, so I don't need to hit the P-switch yet. I probably want to take the P-switch with me, though.
Sure, the flower may or may not be useful later.
Nah, I guess this is just gonna be another Hammer Bro hangout. Good thing I kept my flower!
Hmm... Maybe I should've taken that cape. Well, too late now.
Oh, no. Not that guy! I'd better switch to my flower, so I can try to preserve my feather, in case I get hit.
Ah, so "4-whatever-the-locked-level-is" is a fortress, but that only got 2 votes, so let's play 4-5 first (which had 3 votes).
Looks like I'll be needing a P-switch at some point... or maybe not...
Oh, yeah. Let's see if I can get a perfect in this bonus game! (That was one of the votes.)
Going up! (It was kind of obvious that there was an upper floor in this room.)
To be continued...
YEAH!!! Eat it, ya sack of crap!
Whoa! That was almost dangerous.

...2 votes for 4-whatever-the-locked-level-is (the one just to the right of the 4 sign up there) after I unlock it, 3 votes for 4-4, 3 votes for 4-5, and 9 votes for 4-GH! The ghost house it is, then!
Did I get at least 30 coins?
Close call with that bullet there.
Finally gotcha! Of course, that'll only be temporary, but maybe the room will end before he returns.
Yeah, that's what triggered it. Also, pfft, baseballs... They don't hold a candle to most Touhou bullet patterns!
Did I miss an ON/OFF block somewhere? Well, I kind of have to fly now!
More blue koopas. It's like the game wants me to fly if I'm using Yoshi here!
Let's go see!
Autoscrolling and Lakitu. Okay, I'm pretty sure those weren't in SMB3's tower level.
Wait a minute... I'm going to try something. If I take a hit, I'll stop trying it, but if this works, that would be so awesome!
I think I accidentally hit left and right at the same time back there, pushing me through the right wall, but why did I reappear back on the left? Wait, is the screen-wrap-around in effect here?
Farther down appears to be an airship, a ghost house, a fortress, and a castle that'll have to be gone through before finally reaching King Koopa's castle!
Nope, that wasn't it, but I'm still unhurt, so let's try this one more time! (Epic moment coming up.)
A couple close calls with that Maverick Thwomp...
And I'm guessing that last ON/OFF block is a trap for anyone who's using the shell to hit the blocks here.
Well, I got the Yoshi coin and avoided damage, which is great, but that's not all I wanted to do...
Finish! Also, I chucked the springboard just before hitting the goal on purpose, because I'd rather keep my reserve flower right now.
This also appears to be an "everything wants to kill you" level. I wonder if my no-death streak will end here...
Looks icy. Yep, it's definitely icy.
There's a floating door, and a couple of conflicting arrow signs. Smells like a puzzle level to me!
That opens up the castle, but I'm going to go over to "4-whatever-the-locked-level-is" (AKA 4-Fortress) now.
I hit the fast-forward button on the emulator as I was waiting in these pits, just to save me a couple seconds of real time. (Should I have sped up the video footage in a similar way?)
Uh, oh... This could be bad...
Oh, and I'm not going to bother trying to kill this guy every time I come back to this room. By the time I can kill him, the room's practically over anyway.
Yeah, I thought about cliffhanging you guys there, but I wanted to show off this submap.
Be careful not to get hammered!
Ha! I beat them so fast, I triggered the glitch where it looks like one of them is still hanging around!
And, we're done! Looking back, that level wasn't very long, which is fine by me!
Ooh, better be careful entering this pipe if I don't want my butt poked!
Okay, so the wrap-around effect is intentional at this point. I just happened to trigger it with another glitch by accident down below.
So far, just the usual fortress stuff. Nothing spectacular, yet.
And I'm back here, with this guy again. But, with the ON/OFF switch setting changed, I can now access more things, like this Yoshi coin. (Wow, I'm already at Yoshi coin #4?)
It's also slippery, so be careful of that.
So, until next time, when I start storming through world seven! I'll just leave the overworld music playing for a little while here...
Let's see if this works...
Oh, are we going to be doing bridge building here? Also, I should get that mushroom out of the way right now.
Oh, yeah. It's a perfect!
I wonder if it had a secret exit though. If anyone knows whether this ghost house has a secret exit, let me know! (But, don't tell me where it is if there is one. I'll want to try finding it myself.)
Okay, and this room is autoscrolling, and yes, I will take the extra feather this time.
A Thwomp and spikes. What else is new?
It's Roy! And, I just so happened to have a flower ready for him, so... yeah, he's dead in about two seconds! (Don't even have to really worry about the random bullets.)
Nothing I can do up there, so let's go down the pipe and continue with the level.
Crazy through!
...If I can aim right. Also, thank you green switch blocks!
Okay, this seriously reeks of SMB3's world 5 tower's design now. I wonder if there'll be any pile-driver micro goombas here...
Come on. Get up there!
...If I can aim right!
...?! Uhh... What just happened? LOL, glitch, and it was somewhat helpful too!
So, gray clouds on the overworld mean rain within the level, and also castle music, I guess.
MOOOOOONNN!!!!! Easily reachable with the cape!
Woo. Just barely dodged the flame there! It would be so nice if I could kill that guy...
Nuts. But, I did line up the numbers for a useless extra life!

With the fortress stomped flatter than a pancake, it appears the only level remaining in world 4 is the castle. And, you know what? I'm on a roll here, so I'll go for a little length on today's episode. (Finishing world 4 AFAP was one of the votes after all.)
Also, this map has some cool music. Thanks go to Lightgod87 for informing me what this music is: Mega Man Soccer - Wily Field.
Looks like Roy was trying to outfit the castle for space travel, but it wasn't quite ready yet... Oh, well.
Uh, oh. No Yoshis allowed because they scare the locals!
Something something something, something. Something!
Alright, the room did end before Lakitu returned, and it's boss time!

How I knew that would work: In one of Goron50's recent videos, I saw him slide-kill the fishing boo (using a slope that was lined up perfectly)! And, since cape sliding has the same properties, I knew what I wanted to do when I saw this high platform!
Oh, no. Is this a balloon level? Yeah, this is a balloon level.
Oh, you are so going down for that one, Lakitu!
Aha! I thought that opening on the right side of this room seemed suspicious! Also, I guess I do need a P-switch somewhere.
Okay, I reached the second balloon in time...
Since the first level is red, I guess you guys can vote on whether I go the normal way or the secret way after I clear it.
Yes, but... I apparently fail at grabbing 1-up mushrooms here...
Screen doesn't scroll up. That's good to know.
Gulp! Oh, boy. That shell lasted just barely long enough, but will I be screwed now that I don't have the shell anymore?
Let's see, do I want that turned ON or OFF? Hmm... I'd say I want to leave it turned ON. Just a hunch.

YouTube annotation glitch discovered: I changed my mind about one of the annotations I placed, but apparently, it doesn't acknowledge me deleting it. It disappears from the editor, but it still shows up in the video on the video player page, and it reappears in the annotation editor when I refresh it. I can still edit the annotation, but I can't seem to successfully delete it. (This is that annotation, by the way, which was initially in the middle of the video.)
It's ridiculously easy boss time!
...Or, maybe not. I can easily make that jump. (Heck, it's only eight spaces wide. Capeless Mario could make it!)
I wonder if you guys out there have figured out what I'm really trying to do yet...
So, we've got a red level to begin with, then a battleship.
A key dropped into play from above, and I bet if I hadn't hit the ON/OFF block earlier, the key would've been stuck up there.
Ah, I'm back here, and now I can use the key to enter the door. But, does the P-switch do anything special here?
Doesn't look like it. So, I guess its only real purpose was to be thrown at that one ON/OFF block.
And with that, this bridge is now complete! What awaits us within the giant Bowser head?
Oh, the ceiling's dropping on me! I'd better duck in this coin pit.
The game's just handing me a blue shell. Well, might as well use it, for a little while at least!

Oh, what's this! Aha, that was certainly well-hidden! (But, I think that invisible note block's placement is a bit poor, as someone could easily end up falling down that pit to the right of it as a result.)
I'd love to get rid of that lava lotus as well if I can...
Alright, I'll just shell you!
Can't go back to the left, I don't think. I wonder if there's anything more to the right that I can now reach?
Hmm... Nah, I want to keep my flower this time.
I think I'll try that again...
Gulp!

Hello, and welcome back to Super SIG World 21! Okay, here are the voting results this time: 1 vote for me to get a perfect in the next bonus game I play (I'll try!), 1 vote for me to finish world 4 as fast as possible (I agree!), 1 vote for me to enter the fortress of Yuyuko (She has a fortress?), 1 vote for me to give up, go home, and let Bowser eat the princess (LOL), 1 vote for me to go to a switch level (but which one?), 1 vote for me to download Super Mario War from the forum 72dpiarmy and record it with Camstudio (probably not going to happen...), 2 votes for 3-1 (but of course!)...
I like taking out koopas that way sometimes.
Another blue shell. And, umm...
Yeah, I'm certain I missed an ON/OFF block somewhere, or maybe the level designer screwed up. Good thing there was that blue shell!
I'm gonna burn you good!
Okay, so 4-4 and 4-5 both had 3 votes, so... I'll pick 4-4 next.
Man, these invisible blocks are everywhere, but I think I see the general path I need to take now.
Luigifan22222's translation: "I just finishing climbing the high high mounatin at long last and beat one of The Four Heavenly Kings, Roy. Because he was in such a high place he needed sunglasses!"
